        <hr class="section-heading-spacer">
        <div class="clearfix"></div>
        <h2 class="section-heading">How does matching work?</h2>
        <p class="lead">Find dogs which suit your lifestlye and personality based on five factors!</p>
        <h2>Energy</h2>
        <p class="lead">The more energetic you are the more you'll exercise and play with your dog. More energetic dogs will need more exercise, whereas less energetic ones are happy to lounge around.</p>
        <h2>Confidence</h2>
        <p class="lead">Are you a natural leader and not being hesitant in new situations? A low confidence dog will need more guidance and reassurance from you. </p>
        <h2>Focus</h2>
        <p class="lead">How much focus and determination you have for completing tasks and challenges? More focussed dogs are suited to training.</p>
        <h2>Independence</h2>
        <p class="lead">How much time you spend away from your dog due to work/committments? More independent dogs can keep themselves amused, while more dependent ones are more reliant on your company. </p>
        <h2>Tolerance</h2>
        <p class="lead">How understanding and tolerant you will be if your dog misbehaves or doesn't do something right? More tolerant dogs would be more suited to families with children. </p>
      </div>
      <div class="col-lg-5 col-lg-offset-2 col-sm-6">
